name: D. Digital string maximization
input: InputThe first line of the input consists of an integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 10^4$$$)  — the number of test cases.Each test case consists of a single line consisting of a digital string $$$s$$$ ($$$1 \le |s| \le 2\cdot 10^5$$$), where $$$|s|$$$ denotes the length of $$$s$$$. The string does not contain leading zeroes.It is guaranteed that the sum of $$$|s|$$$ of all test cases doesn't exceed $$$2\cdot 10^5$$$.
output: OutputFor each test case, print the answer on a separate line.
